initial_story:
The Eurovision Song Contest is just around the corner and this year, it's taking place in Malmo, Sweden.

You can find out all about the event right here.

The UK's entry for 2024 is Olly Alexander who'll be performing his song, Dizzy.

But how's he feeling ahead of the big night, where he'll perform in front of 200 million people!

De-Graft sat down with him to find out all about his preparation for the competition.

The Eurovision Song contest Grand Final will be shown on BBC One and iPlayer on Saturday 11 May.
stories: Olly Alexander told De-Graft that he's been preparing for months, rehearsing his dance routine and perfecting his vocals. "I've been working with a choreographer to get the moves just right, and I've been doing vocal warm-ups every day to make sure my voice is in top condition," he said.

"I was thinking we could do a mashup of some of our biggest hits, and then have the crowd join in on the chorus," Olly said, his enthusiasm growing. "And maybe even have a special guest star join us on stage for a few songs."
